close_reason: "Plan workflow exposed in SDK cli-contracts (PLAN_FLAG_CONTRACTS + plan tool action schema), MCP server (pm_plan tool + plan action routing + instructions), Codex/Claude planner docs/skills, docs/COMMANDS.md + docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md, and dogfood-package-first.mjs (Plan lifecycle assertions). pm contracts --command plan --flags-only returns full flag list; pm plan registered as a top-level command; MCP pm_plan operational end-to-end."
body: "Expose the Plan item type and `pm plan` workflow through agent-facing integration surfaces.\n\nScope:\n- Update SDK contracts and MCP/tool schemas so agents can discover Plan support and dedicated plan actions without reading full help text.\n- Update Codex and Claude plugin assets so slash commands/skills use `pm plan` rather than ad-hoc planner docs once the command exists.\n- Update docs/help/examples with progressive-disclosure recipes for agent harnesses.\n- Add dogfood coverage that creates a Plan, adds steps, links related/dependency pm items, approves/materializes selected steps, and verifies search/readback.\n\nAgent harness examples required:\n- Codex-style: create a self-contained Plan with progress, decisions, validation, and resume context; update steps as implementation proceeds.\n- Claude-style: read-only planning before approval; TaskCreate/TaskUpdate equivalent mapping to Plan steps.\n- Cursor-style: codebase research, clarifying questions, file path/code references, editable steps, and saved future context.\n\nOutput and documentation requirements:\n- Help should make `pm plan` the shortest path for agents needing durable plans.\n- Contracts should expose flags and JSON shapes for all `pm plan` subcommands.\n- MCP should surface plan actions with compact schema descriptions and deterministic response fields.\n- Plugin docs must avoid implying `Plan` is only a Claude/Codex artifact; it is a pm-native item type.\n- Dogfood should assert low-token `pm plan show --fields` output and search discoverability.\n\nAcceptance:\n- SDK/MCP/plugin/help/docs surfaces all mention Plan and `pm plan` consistently.\n- Packed CLI smoke or package-first dogfood covers the workflow.\n- Future agents can discover usage via `pm contracts`, `pm help`, plugin slash commands, and search."
